    "review_comment": [
      "In this playbook, only the non-failed host executes the task after clear_host_errors:\r\n```yaml\r\n---\r\n- hosts: localhost\r\n  gather_facts: no\r\n  tasks:\r\n    - add_host: name={{ item }} ansible_connection=local\r\n      loop: [h1, h2]\r\n\r\n- hosts: h1,h2\r\n  gather_facts: no\r\n  handlers:\r\n    - name: sometimes_fail\r\n      fail:\r\n      when: 'inventory_hostname == \"h1\"'\r\n  tasks:\r\n    - command: echo\r\n      notify: sometimes_fail\r\n    - meta: flush_handlers\r\n    - meta: clear_host_errors\r\n    - debug: msg='should run for both hosts'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis seems to fix it:\r\n```suggestion\r\n        if state.fail_state == FailedStates.HANDLERS:\r\n            state.run_state = state.pre_flushing_run_state\r\n            state.pre_flushing_run_state = None\r\n\r\n        state.fail_state = FailedStates.NONE\r\n```\r\n",
      "Actually. The behavior in this PR (for handler failure/task failure) is the same as failure in a normal task on devel. Not sure if this is just unintuitive to me alone or a bug, but not something that needs to be addressed in this PR.\r\n\r\nAfter thinking about it more, making a handler failure recoverable via clear_host_errors doesn't make sense since it's the last iterator state. Having a flush_handlers midplay is confusing me.",
      "devel:\r\n```\r\nPLAY [h1,h2] *********************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [command] *******************************************************************************************************\r\nchanged: [h2]\r\nchanged: [h1]\r\n\r\nTASK [meta] **********************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nRUNNING HANDLER [sometimes_fail] *************************************************************************************\r\nskipping: [h2]\r\nfatal: [h1]: FAILED! => {\"changed\": false, \"msg\": \"Failed as requested from task\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\nthis PR as is, better:\r\n```\r\nPLAY [h1,h2] *********************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [command] *******************************************************************************************************\r\nchanged: [h2]\r\nchanged: [h1]\r\n\r\nTASK [meta] **********************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [meta] **********************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nRUNNING HANDLER [sometimes_fail] *************************************************************************************\r\nfatal: [h1]: FAILED! => {\"changed\": false, \"msg\": \"Failed as requested from task\"}\r\nskipping: [h2]\r\n\r\nTASK [meta] **********************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [debug] *********************************************************************************************************\r\nok: [h2] => {\r\n    \"msg\": \"should run for both hosts\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nthis PR with proposed fix, probably correct\r\n```\r\nPLAY [h1,h2] *********************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [command] *******************************************************************************************************\r\nchanged: [h2]\r\nchanged: [h1]\r\n\r\nTASK [meta] **********************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [meta] **********************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nRUNNING HANDLER [sometimes_fail] *************************************************************************************\r\nfatal: [h1]: FAILED! => {\"changed\": false, \"msg\": \"Failed as requested from task\"}\r\nskipping: [h2]\r\n\r\nTASK [meta] **********************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [debug] *********************************************************************************************************\r\nok: [h2] => {\r\n    \"msg\": \"should run for both hosts\"\r\n}\r\n\r\nTASK [meta] **********************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [debug] *********************************************************************************************************\r\nok: [h1] => {\r\n    \"msg\": \"should run for both hosts\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think your fix is the correct thing to do.\r\n\r\n> After thinking about it more, making a handler failure recoverable via clear_host_errors doesn't make sense since it's the last iterator state. Having a flush_handlers midplay is confusing me.\r\n\r\nThe confusing part is that technically `IteratingStates.HANDLERS` is actually not the last iterator state. If you look at the state machine in the `PlayIterator` there is nothing that would advance the state into `IteratingStates.HANDLERS`, no `state.run_state = IteratingStates.HANDLERS`. Only thing that makes it \"last\" is that we have implicit `flush_handlers` tasks after each section. And `flush_handlers` is the only way for `PlayIterator` to get into `IteratingStates.HANDLERS` state. And what makes this hard (and confusing) is that you can run `flush_handlers` anywhere in the play \ud83e\udd2f ",
      "Although I wonder if we should think of this as clear_host_errors issue and deal with it in a separate PR?",
      "Fixing as a separate PR would be fine to me, totally your call. It is closer to the behavior that I'd expect than devel. If you replace the notify/flush_handlers with a failed task:\r\n```yaml\r\n    # - command: echo\r\n    #   notify: sometimes_fail\r\n    # - meta: flush_handlers\r\n    - fail:\r\n      when: \"inventory_hostname == 'h1'\"\r\n```\r\nthe behavior on devel matches this branch (the final `- debug: msg='should run for both hosts'` still only runs for h2), and that definitely seems like a bug to me.\r\n\r\nThen I guess rescue/always should also work for handler failures if flush_handlers is in a block (?). This example has the same issue of unrecoverable handler failure (but works on devel):\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\n  tasks:\r\n  - block:\r\n      - command: echo\r\n        notify: sometimes_fail\r\n      - meta: flush_handlers\r\n    rescue:\r\n      - debug: msg='rescue h1'\r\n  - debug: msg='should run for both hosts'\r\n```\r\n\r\nOn devel:\r\n```\r\nPLAY [localhost] ************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [add_host] *************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\nchanged: [localhost] => (item=h1)\r\nchanged: [localhost] => (item=h2)\r\n\r\nPLAY [h1,h2] ****************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [command] **************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\nchanged: [h1]\r\nchanged: [h2]\r\n\r\nTASK [meta] *****************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nRUNNING HANDLER [sometimes_fail] ********************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\nfatal: [h1]: FAILED! => {\"changed\": false, \"msg\": \"Failed as requested from task\"}\r\nskipping: [h2]\r\n\r\nTASK [debug] ****************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\nok: [h1] => {\r\n    \"msg\": \"Hello world!\"\r\n}\r\n\r\nTASK [debug] ****************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\nok: [h1] => {\r\n    \"msg\": \"should run for both hosts\"\r\n}\r\nok: [h2] => {\r\n    \"msg\": \"should run for both hosts\"\r\n}\r\n\r\nPLAY RECAP ******************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\nh1                         : ok=3    changed=1    unreachable=0    failed=0    skipped=0    rescued=1    ignored=0   \r\nh2                         : ok=2    changed=1    unreachable=0    failed=0    skipped=1    rescued=0    ignored=0   \r\nlocalhost                  : ok=1    changed=1    unreachable=0    failed=0    skipped=0    rescued=0    ignored=0 \r\n```\r\n\r\nThis branch:\r\n```\r\nPLAY [localhost] ************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [add_host] *************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\nchanged: [localhost] => (item=h1)\r\nchanged: [localhost] => (item=h2)\r\n\r\nPLAY [h1,h2] ****************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [command] **************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\nchanged: [h2]\r\nchanged: [h1]\r\n\r\nTASK [meta] *****************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nTASK [meta] *****************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nRUNNING HANDLER [sometimes_fail] ********************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\nfatal: [h1]: FAILED! => {\"changed\": false, \"msg\": \"Failed as requested from task\"}\r\nskipping: [h2]\r\n\r\nTASK [debug] ****************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\nok: [h2] => {\r\n    \"msg\": \"should run for both hosts\"\r\n}\r\n\r\nPLAY RECAP ******************************************************************************************************************************************************************************\r\nh1                         : ok=1    changed=1    unreachable=0    failed=1    skipped=0    rescued=0    ignored=0   \r\nh2                         : ok=2    changed=1    unreachable=0    failed=0    skipped=1    rescued=0    ignored=0   \r\nlocalhost                  : ok=1    changed=1    unreachable=0    failed=0    skipped=0    rescued=0    ignored=0 \r\n```",
      "Pushed https://github.com/ansible/ansible/pull/77955/commits/8fa40982a960b70eb8341e3e8ebd4146a27c6451 as a fix, probably needs a test too. We'll see if `ci_complete` passes.\r\n\r\nNice find!",
      "`ci_complete` passed on the above commit and I added a test for it.",
